<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1285</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003H</addr><route>erct-003H.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003H.agda" type="external">erct-003H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1286</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002X" href="erct-002X.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-004A" href="erct-004A.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1287</anchor>  <addr>erct-003A</addr><route>erct-003A.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relating different kinds of equivalence</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1288</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002E</addr><route>erct-002E.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">Invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002E.agda" type="external">erct-002E.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1289</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>\epsilon   \colon  f \circ  f ^{-1}  =  1_{ B }</tex> be the counit of the <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Given <tex>b:B</tex>, we must show that the fiber of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x,  \epsilon  x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and the required paths can be constructed via the <link href="erct-001R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001R" title="Path object structure on fibers">univalence principle for fibers</link> using the unit <tex>\eta \colon  f ^{-1} \circ  f =  1_{ A }</tex>, the coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f</tex>, and the <link href="erct-001V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001V" title="Naturality of homotopies">naturality of homotopies</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1290</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002F</addr><route>erct-002F.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002F.agda" type="external">erct-002F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1291</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a retraction <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. To construct <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>r</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f</tex>, we use the identification between any two elements of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>fx</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1292</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002G</addr><route>erct-002G.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002G.agda" type="external">erct-002G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1293</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a section <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. The witness <tex>h_s \colon  f \circ  s \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s</tex> as a section of <tex>f</tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1294</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002H</addr><route>erct-002H.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002H.agda" type="external">erct-002H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1295</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Because <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible maps</link> are both <link href="erct-002F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002F" title="Contractible maps are sections">sections</link> and <link href="erct-002G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002G" title="Contractible maps are retractions">retractions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1296</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002M</addr><route>erct-002M.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002M.agda" type="external">erct-002M.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1297</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <link href="erct-002C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002C" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses">can be improved</link> to a <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">coherent inverse</link>, and <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">any coherently invertible map</link> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1298</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002N</addr><route>erct-002N.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002N.agda" type="external">erct-002N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1299</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>As <link href="erct-002D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002D" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses">biinvertible maps are quasi-invertible</link> and <link href="erct-002M.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002M" title="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible">quasi-invertible maps are contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1300</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002O</addr><route>erct-002O.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002O.agda" type="external">erct-002O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the postcomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f \circ  - \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  A \right ) \mathclose {} \to   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  B \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1301</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section and retraction</link> are built using by postcomposing with the designated <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section and retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>; the witnesses for the postcomposition <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> are constructed using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for function spaces</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1302</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002P</addr><route>erct-002P.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Restriction along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002P.agda" type="external">erct-002P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the precomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( - \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( B \to  C \right ) \mathclose {} \to \mathopen {} \left ( A \to  C \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1303</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the corresponding result for <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">pushforward along biinvertible maps</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1304</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002W</addr><route>erct-002W.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002W.agda" type="external">erct-002W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1305</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must show that each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">proposition</link>; in fact, each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">contractible</link> as <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">biinvertible maps are contractible</link>, and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1306</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr><route>erct-002X.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1307</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1308</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003H</addr><route>erct-003H.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003H.agda" type="external">erct-003H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1309</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002X" href="erct-002X.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-004A" href="erct-004A.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1310</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0048</addr><route>erct-0048.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">Embeddings</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0048.agda" type="external">erct-0048.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1311</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must check that for every <tex>b:B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> at <tex>b</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Fixing <tex>u_0,u_1: \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, b</tex> we must check that <tex>u_0=u_1</tex>. We let <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_0,p_0 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_0</tex> and <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_1,p_1 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_1</tex> so that we have <tex>p_0 \colon  fa_0=b</tex> and <tex>p_1 \colon  fa_1=b</tex>. Invoking the <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure on <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> (<ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/>), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \psi &amp; \colon  p_0 =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1    \end {aligned}  </tex>

  <p>As <tex>f</tex> is an <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">embedding</link>, the map <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  a_0 = a_1  \to  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> has an <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1} , \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>

 <p>Let <tex>\alpha   \colon  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> be the concatenation <tex>p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Therefore we may define:</p>

 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \phi &amp;: \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1}   \alpha     \end {aligned}  </tex>

 <p>To define <tex>\psi   \colon  p_0= \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1</tex> we use the counit of our <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> as we have <tex>\epsilon   \alpha   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi  = p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <tex>p_1</tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1312</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0049</addr><route>erct-0049.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Propositional maps</link> are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda" type="external">erct-0049.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1313</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>x,y:A</tex> we must show that <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x = y  \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002D" href="erct-002D.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to exhibit a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link> to <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f }</tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> need not be identical).</p>

 <p>We first define the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> <tex>s_{x,y} \colon  fx = fy  \to  x = y</tex>. Because <tex>f</tex> is assumed to be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, we have by <ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/> an assignment <tex>\phi _{x,y}:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. We therefore define <tex>s_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .1</tex>; the witness of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sectionhood</link> can be constructed using <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .2</tex> modulo some identification algebra.</p>

 <p>To construct the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> <tex>r_{x,y} \colon  fx=fy \to  x = y</tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <tex>\psi _{x,y}: \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }  \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and we define <tex>r_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. It remains to show that for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> and <tex>h \colon  x =y</tex>, we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} =h</tex>. By induction on <tex>h</tex> it suffices to show that for all <tex>x:A</tex> we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex>. We will deduce that <tex>\psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex> from our assumption that <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link> and thus <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">fibred in sets</link> via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1314</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-004A</addr><route>erct-004A.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-004A.agda" type="external">erct-004A.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1315</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002W" href="erct-002W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-0049" href="erct-0049.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1316</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Y</addr><route>erct-002Y.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Y.agda" type="external">erct-002Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1317</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>b:B</tex>, we must check that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link>; because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link> by <ref addr="erct-0048" href="erct-0048.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> to observe that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <em>inhabited</em> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1318</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002Z</addr><route>erct-002Z.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Z.agda" type="external">erct-002Z.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1319</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002Y" href="erct-002Y.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; by <ref addr="erct-002H" href="erct-002H.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1320</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-004A</addr><route>erct-004A.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-004A.agda" type="external">erct-004A.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1321</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-004A</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002W" href="erct-002W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-0049" href="erct-0049.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1322</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003F</addr><route>erct-003F.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Bijection</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003F.agda" type="external">erct-003F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>bijective</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1323</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr><route>erct-002X.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1324</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-002X</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1325</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr><route>erct-000U.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <em><strong>biinvertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1326</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003I</addr><route>erct-003I.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">Equivalence</link> between <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link> and <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003I.agda" type="external">erct-003I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The correspondence between <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> maps of <ref addr="erct-003H" href="erct-003H.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-002Z" href="erct-002Z.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> lifts to an <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalence</link> from the type of <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link> to the type of <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link>.</p>
 
   
